                  <div class="wysiwyg-wrapper">
                    <div><span style="font-size: 16px">Hi-Rez Studios is now accepting qualified UI / UX Programming Intern applicants for our Summer Internship Program for our Unannounced Project in Alpharetta, Georgia! </span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="font-size: 12pt">This will be a paid, seasonal employee. The deadline to submit all application materials is Feb 28, 2019. &nbsp;Internship selections will be made and announced by April 1, 2019, with the Intern work program starting mid May, 2019, ending mid-August, 2019 (actual dates to be determined).</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="font-size: 12pt">Come join the creator of the critically acclaimed SMITE; Paladins; Tribes: Ascend; and Global Agenda as we embark on exciting new game projects!</span></div><p class="title">What our UI / UX Programming Interns do:</p><li>Design, prototype, code, and unit test User Interface enhancements, features, and fixes for our Unannounced Project.</li><li>Implement UI screens, HUD elements, and functionality using Unreal Engine 4.</li><p class="title">What we are looking for:</p><li>Must be able to travel effectively to and from studio on a daily basis.</li><li>Must be currently enrolled in (documented as a "Junior" or higher grade level) - or recently graduated &nbsp;of - an accredited college, university, or school of art.</li><li>Currently carrying or graduated with a G.P.A. of 3.5 or higher (and provide documentation). </li><li>At least one professional Letter of Reference from a manager, supervisor, professor or instructor; outlining how they know you, and why you should be considered for this position.</li><li>Current resume.</li><li>Cover letter.</li><li>Portfolio and/or Website displaying applicable work.</li><li>Authorized to work in the U.S.</li><li>Good communication skills, and a team player.</li><p class="title">Even better candidates:</p><li>Experience within Unreal Engine 4 is a plus.</li><li>Background or experience in Gaming.</li><li>Experience with C++, Python, or related languages.</li><li>Experience with web development technologies (HTML5, CSS, JavaScript, SCSS).</li><li>Experience with Photoshop.</li>                  </div>
                  <div class="flex-wrapper">
                    <a href="https://jobs.lever.co/hirezstudios/fa404b44-d723-416a-9526-dda0dbb5c180/apply" target="_blank" class="button white">Candidate-se agora</a>
                  </div>
